One97 Communications Ltd,

259
00:11:28,002 --> 00:11:32,729
there is no operational segregation 
between it and Paytm Payments Bank.

260
00:11:32,729 --> 00:11:34,921
There was cash flow between the two,

261
00:11:34,921 --> 00:11:37,617
which was not disclosed in the financial statements.

262
00:11:37,617 --> 00:11:41,132
So many rules and regulations were ignored.

263
00:11:41,132 --> 00:11:46,262
Is the arrogance of their CEO Vijay Shekhar Sharma 
responsible for this to some extent?

264
00:11:46,262 --> 00:11:48,493
He gave many interviews to media channels

265
00:11:48,493 --> 00:11:51,495
this arrogance was seen in his words in those interviews.

266
00:11:51,495 --> 00:11:54,814
"If you fundamentally believe 
that Paytm is #3 payment player,

267
00:11:54,814 --> 00:11:56,672
that is where the beginning of the problem is

268
00:11:56,672 --> 00:11:57,340
in understanding."

269
00:11:57,340 --> 00:11:58,888
"I'm surprised that people don't know this

270
00:11:58,888 --> 00:11:59,734
in this country, but

271
00:11:59,734 --> 00:12:01,131
we make profit, so it is."

272
00:12:01,131 --> 00:12:02,579
"Somebody who has not met us

273
00:12:02,579 --> 00:12:03,720
and has an opinion on us

274
00:12:03,720 --> 00:12:04,756
is not my opinion

275
00:12:04,756 --> 00:12:05,819
to keep an opinion on that."

276
00:12:06,000 --> 00:12:08,304
After RBI's announcement on 31st January,

277
00:12:08,304 --> 00:12:09,599
a commotion broke out.

278
00:12:09,599 --> 00:12:13,657
People started taking out 
the money they had invested in Paytm.

279
00:12:13,657 --> 00:12:17,210
So, Paytm's stock crashed very fast.

280
00:12:17,210 --> 00:12:18,906
To calm people down,

281
00:12:18,906 --> 00:12:21,863
Paytm posted on its social media handles that

282
00:12:21,863 --> 00:12:23,429
there was nothing wrong.

283
00:12:23,429 --> 00:12:26,237
On 2nd February, Vijay Shekhar Sharma tweeted this.

284
00:12:26,237 --> 00:12:27,355
"To every Paytmer,

285
00:12:27,355 --> 00:12:28,738
Your favourite app is working,

286
00:12:28,738 --> 00:12:31,372
will keep working beyond 29th February as usual...

287
00:12:31,372 --> 00:12:33,456
For every challenge, there is a solution

288
00:12:33,456 --> 00:12:35,654
and we are sincerely committed to serve our nation

289
00:12:35,654 --> 00:12:36,530
in full compliance. 

290
00:12:36,530 --> 00:12:38,867
India will keep winning global accolades 

291
00:12:38,867 --> 00:12:41,637
in payment innovation and 
inclusion in financial services." 

292
00:12:41,843 --> 00:12:43,449
As you can see, once again,

293
00:12:43,449 --> 00:12:45,675
patriotism was used as a shield here.

294
00:12:45,675 --> 00:12:47,237
'Don't see us as a company,

295
00:12:47,237 --> 00:12:49,077
see us as patriots serving the nation.'

296
00:12:49,077 --> 00:12:51,165
Using India as the shield

297
00:12:51,165 --> 00:12:52,843
Paytm tried to hide behind it.

298
00:12:52,843 --> 00:12:54,652
This reminds me of a quote.

299
00:12:54,652 --> 00:12:58,049
"Patriotism is the last refuge of a scoundrel."

300
00:12:58,049 --> 00:12:59,429
You must have heard this quote.

301
00:12:59,429 --> 00:13:03,087
In my opinion, we should be wary of such companies

302
00:13:03,087 --> 00:13:05,636
which rely too heavily on nationalism.

303
00:13:05,636 --> 00:13:08,593
A few years ago, there was a phone Freedom 251.

304
00:13:08,825 --> 00:13:11,071
They printed India's national flag on the back of the phone.

305
00:13:11,071 --> 00:13:14,410
It was sold as the 'world's cheapest phone'

306
00:13:14,410 --> 00:13:15,666
but it turned out to be a big scam.

307
00:13:15,666 --> 00:13:18,253
If a company's products and services

308
00:13:18,253 --> 00:13:19,404
have intrinsic value,

309
00:13:19,404 --> 00:13:21,749
they sell it by promoting those values.

310
00:13:22,162 --> 00:13:25,572
But if they don't have much to say 
about their products or services,

311
00:13:25,572 --> 00:13:28,385
then patriotism is used as a selling point.

312
00:13:28,720 --> 00:13:30,349
Urging you to buy their product

313
00:13:30,349 --> 00:13:31,384
just because they are Indian.

314
00:13:31,384 --> 00:13:32,943
Because they are an Indian company,

315
00:13:32,943 --> 00:13:34,609
they use it as the only reason 
why you should buy their product.

316
00:13:34,609 --> 00:13:36,251
Anyways, if we come back to Paytm,

317
00:13:36,251 --> 00:13:38,601
the question is, what will happen next?

318
00:13:38,601 --> 00:13:40,321
Internally, the employees of the company

319
00:13:40,321 --> 00:13:42,260
are facing a lot of uncertainty.

320
00:13:42,260 --> 00:13:44,134
They are not getting much clarity from the leadership

321
00:13:44,134 --> 00:13:45,429
about what will happen next.

322
00:13:45,429 --> 00:13:47,014
Economic Times reported that

323
00:13:47,014 --> 00:13:49,094
an executive of the company told them that

324
00:13:49,094 --> 00:13:51,768
their business model might change.

325
00:13:51,768 --> 00:13:53,318
Now, instead of being a bank,

326
00:13:53,318 --> 00:13:55,597
they might try to become a third-party payments app.

327
00:13:55,597 --> 00:13:58,286
So they will have to change 
some things on the back end.

328
00:13:58,286 --> 00:14:00,705
And they will have to make the change in a limited time.

329
00:14:00,705 --> 00:14:02,553
If you look at Paytm's annual report,

330
00:14:02,553 --> 00:14:05,599
to check how much has it earned each year,

331
00:14:05,599 --> 00:14:07,528
you will see that it has always been

332
00:14:07,528 --> 00:14:09,375
a loss-making company since

333
00:14:09,375 --> 00:14:11,396
its shares were listed on the stock market.

334
00:14:11,396 --> 00:14:12,393
Look at this chart,

335
00:14:12,393 --> 00:14:15,968
in FY 2021, the company incurred a loss of ₹16 billion.

336
00:14:16,278 --> 00:14:18,724
In FY 2022, a loss of ₹15 billion.

337
00:14:19,265 --> 00:14:22,364
In FY 2023, a loss of ₹1.7 billion.

338
00:14:22,364 --> 00:14:24,141
The good news was that year after year

339
00:14:24,141 --> 00:14:26,501
the company's losses were decreasing.

340
00:14:26,501 --> 00:14:28,468
So, it could have been expected that next year,

341
00:14:28,468 --> 00:14:30,593
that is, this year, in FY 2024,

342
00:14:30,593 --> 00:14:32,899
the company would earn its first profit.

343
00:14:32,899 --> 00:14:35,702
But now, after everything that has happened,

344
00:14:35,702 --> 00:14:36,903
it seems difficult.

345
00:14:36,903 --> 00:14:38,978
The company expects that this year,

346
00:14:38,978 --> 00:14:41,840
the company's loss could increase by ₹3 billion to ₹5 billion.

347
00:14:41,840 --> 00:14:44,721
Paytm has revealed this to the public,

348
00:14:44,721 --> 00:14:48,025
saying that they will now comply 
with the guidelines issued by RBI.

349
00:14:48,025 --> 00:14:49,929
But after this announcement,

350
00:14:49,929 --> 00:14:51,953
the company's stock price fell further.

351
00:14:51,953 --> 00:14:54,031
"What is the path to profitability Vijay?

352
00:14:54,031 --> 00:14:56,877
What is... by when will Paytm make money?"

353
00:14:56,877 --> 00:14:59,250
"Make more money? 
By making more money.

354
00:14:59,250 --> 00:15:00,781
By making more money!"

355
00:15:01,039 --> 00:15:04,977
Vijay Shekhar Sharma will have to come up 
with better answers to these questions

356
00:15:04,977 --> 00:15:06,957
if he wants to convince people.

357
00:15:06,957 --> 00:15:08,714
Actually, convincing people

358
00:15:08,714 --> 00:15:12,187
will be the biggest challenge for Paytm.

359
00:15:12,187 --> 00:15:15,732
An average person is very picky about choosing a company.

360
00:15:15,732 --> 00:15:18,381
And public's trust plays an important role here.

361
00:15:18,381 --> 00:15:20,298
Once people choose their toothpaste,

362
00:15:20,298 --> 00:15:24,649
they decide that they will use 
that company's toothpaste forever.

363
00:15:24,649 --> 00:15:26,437
They don't change their mind easily.

364
00:15:26,437 --> 00:15:29,309
Here, they will be more cautious as this 
involves their money and banking abilities. 

365
00:15:29,309 --> 00:15:31,299
Bringing customers back

366
00:15:31,299 --> 00:15:33,331
won't be easy for Paytm.

367
00:15:33,331 --> 00:15:35,462
But convincing customers will come later.

368
00:15:35,462 --> 00:15:38,200
First, Paytm will have to convince RBI.

369
00:15:38,200 --> 00:15:39,754
That won't be an easy task.

370
00:15:39,754 --> 00:15:40,925
But there is light at the end of the tunnel,

371
00:15:40,925 --> 00:15:43,543
a way to get out of this can be 

372
00:15:43,543 --> 00:15:45,220
to have another company

373
00:15:45,220 --> 00:15:47,372
buy Paytm's wallet business.

374
00:15:47,372 --> 00:15:49,591
A Business Standard report suggests that

375
00:15:49,591 --> 00:15:52,488
HDFC Bank and Jio Financial Services

376
00:15:52,488 --> 00:15:54,549
might just do this.

377
00:15:54,549 --> 00:15:56,847
But Jio has denied this speculation

378
00:15:56,847 --> 00:15:59,179
saying that they have no intention of doing so.

379
00:15:59,179 --> 00:16:02,256
And anyway, before executing such a sale,

380
00:16:02,256 --> 00:16:04,083
they'd need RBI's approval.

